      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against N=11 physical specimens tested across two independent laboratories. Mean percent difference 4.8%; E/uval = 1.31, within the pre-established acceptance bound of 1.96. The observational dataset was assembled from routine product-characterization records maintained by DePuy Synthes and FDA; specimens were drawn from production lots without prospective randomisation or controlled environmental conditioning. The activity is characterised here as an observational study because specimen selection and test sequencing followed historical laboratory scheduling rather than a pre-registered experimental protocol. The agreement between FEA predictions and the observational measurements is strong across all three QoIs, supporting the inference that the model is sufficiently credible for the intended COU.",
