        "name": "F1717 compression-bending bench data collection — production-lot observational series",
        "description": "Compression-bending load-displacement data were obtained from eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production inventory. Tests were performed on a servo-hydraulic load frame following ASTM F1717 displacement-control protocol at 5 mm/min. Specimen selection was not prospectively randomised; constructs were drawn from available stock at two sites (FDA CDRH biomechanics laboratory and an OEM internal test facility) according to routine scheduling. Environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) were recorded post-hoc from facility logs rather than actively controlled. Because specimen allocation and environmental monitoring were retrospective rather than prospectively designed, this data-collection episode is classified as an observational study rather than a fully controlled experiment.",
